Bring a #saucepan{} of @water{1%large potful} up to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the @Rigatoni Pasta{200%g}.

When boiling, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{200%g} and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan and drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm sized chunks or as small as you can.

Halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Green Chilli{1} lengthways, deseed then finely chop.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

When the oil is hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, bell pepper and chopped onion and cook until the beef is browned and the veggies tender, ~{5-6%mins}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

When cooked, add the garlic and @Worcester Sauce{15%ml}. Cook stirring frequently ~{1%minute}.

Once the garlic has cooked, add the @Tomato Passata{1} and @Beef Stock Powder{1}. Bring to a boil and reduce the heat to a simmer. Cook until thickened, ~{8-10%mins}.

Once everything has cooked, pop the @BBQ Sauce{32%g} into the pan with the beef and bring to the boil. Season the beef to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pop the drained pasta into the pan with the beef and mix well to combine and remove from the heat.

Share the smoky beef pasta between your #bowls{}. Top with the grated cheese and a sprinkle of green chilli (careful it's hot, add less if you don't like heat). Enjoy!